sample.title: Want To ‚ÄòInvest' In OpenAI or SpaceX? What To Know About Tokenization
sample.description:
Private companies like OpenAI and SpaceX have captured enormous investor enthusiasm in recent years, driving up their valuations. Yet because they‚Äôre privately held, they‚Äôve remained largely inaccessible to ordinary investors. Now a new approached called tokenization could change that by giving retail investors access to investments aligned with the performance of private companies. But despite its appeal, some worry that tokenizing private companies could be a way to bypass longstanding regulations meant to protect investors.

sample.title: BBC confronts man bulk-buying and reselling UK driving tests  | BBC News
sample.description:
Driving instructors are being offered kickbacks of up to ¬£250 a month to sell their official test-booking login details to touts, a BBC investigation has found.
 
Touts use these login details to book driving tests in bulk and sell them to learners on WhatsApp and Facebook, charging as much as ¬£500 for tests that should cost no more than ¬£75. 
 
This makes it harder for learners to book through legitimate routes and adds to already lengthy waiting times.
 
The BBC confronted Anil Ahmed, who buys driving instructors' login details and then sells tests online at a mark-up. He says the claims we put to him are a "complete fabrication".
 
Transport Secretary Heidi Alexander recently announced plans to change driving test rules, which it is hoped will stop touts and reduce the backlog. Only learners - not instructors - will be able to book test slots from spring 2026.
